 surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":5,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":36,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger FitzEllis was born in 1254, in Corston, Wiltshire, England, his father, William FitzEllis III, was 29 and his mother, Margaret, was 23. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Dama Fitzellis. He died in 1302, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1254–1302":"1254–1302","1254–Male":"1254–Surnud","1255–Female":"1255–Surnud","1279–1318":"1279–1318","1280–Female":"1280–Surnud","1225–1262":"1225–1262","1231–Female":"1231–Surnud","about 1280":"umbes 1280","1259":"1259","1302":"1302","1225":"1225","1279":"1279","1255":"1255","1254":"1254","1231":"1231","1262":"1262","1280":"1280","1318":"1318","1290":"1290","Corston, Wiltshire, Eng.":"Corston, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Corston, Somerset, England":"Corston, Somerset, England","England":"England","Corston, Wiltshire, England":"Corston, Wiltshire, England"},"fi":{"1254–1302":"1254–1302","1254–Male":"1254–Kuollut","1255–Female":"1255–Kuollut","1279–1318":"1279–1318","1280–Female":"1280–Kuollut","1225–1262":"1225–1262","1231–Female":"1231–Kuollut","about 1280":"noin 1280","1259":"1259","1302":"1302","1225":"1225","1279":"1279","1255":"1255","1254":"1254","1231":"1231","1262":"1262","1280":"1280","1318":"1318","1290":"1290","Corston, Wiltshire, Eng.":"Corston, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Corston, Somerset, England